
    Installation

 Typically "./configure && make install".
 
 See also:
   <http://code.google.com/p/cclive/wiki/HowtoInstall>


    Optional Packages

 --with-man (default)
    Whether the manual page should be installed. --without-man disables.

 --enable-sigwinch
    If enabled, cclive handles SIGWINCH signal to resize progressbar to
    match the terminal width. BSD/Linux specific, may work on other
    Unix-like systems.

    Disabled by default.

 --with-perl
    Build cclive with embedded Perl interpreter. Used to parse
    video page <title> tags. Enables --title* program options.
    
    Note that you will also need the HTML::Tokenizer Perl module.

    Disabled by default.


    Prerequisites

 * libcurl (7.18.0+)

    Optional

 * Perl 5.8+ with HTML::TokeParser module. See --with-perl above.


            Examples

 # ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --without-sigwinch
 # make install
